Has anyone seen photonvision not let you select the camera processing mode? We are using an OrangePi 5 with two Arducam OV2981 and we have the ability to receive 2D data, but not 3D data. Is there something we are just overlooking? Any help would be appreciated.

Hello!

Are your cameras calibrated? If so, have you selected the resolution that you calibrated them at? You currently have 800x600 selected down at the bottom. You can check your calibration, and the resolution at which you calibrated, in the “Camera” tab.

Photonvision will not allow you to select 3D Mode if calibration at the selected resolution has not been completed as it is a prerequisite for 3D detection.
